  "citation_spans": [
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Non-major chromosomal rearrangements rarely accompanying NPM mutations are, therefore, likely to be secondary events."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_2]",
      "span_text": "A striking feature of NPMc ϩ gene-expression signature is the activation of numerous members of the homeodomain-containing family of transcription factors, including HOX and TALE genes, some of which are oncogenes in myeloid leukemias and implicated in hematopoietic development. 14 Several HOX genes are highly expressed in hematopoietic stem cells (HSCs), and their expression decreases with differentiation."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_3]",
      "span_text": "Notably, NPMc ϩ AMLs also display induction of the Notch1-ligand JAG1 and repression of CDKN2C/ p18-INK4C, which are associated to expansion of the HSC pool. Repression of the HSC-associated genes CD34 and CD133/PROM1 is not necessarily in contrast with this view, since a HSC subpopulation negative for both lineage-and HSC-associated markers has been identified. Consistent with the view that NPMc ϩ AMLs might derive from a HSC, they show a wide FAB morphologic spectrum and frequent multilineage involvement. A similar HOX signature was previously reported in an uncharacterized subset of AML with normal karyotype. We demonstrate that this is a specific feature of NPMc ϩ AMLs."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_4]",
      "span_text": "Notably, NPMc ϩ AMLs also display induction of the Notch1-ligand JAG1 and repression of CDKN2C/ p18-INK4C, which are associated to expansion of the HSC pool. Repression of the HSC-associated genes CD34 and CD133/PROM1 is not necessarily in contrast with this view, since a HSC subpopulation negative for both lineage-and HSC-associated markers has been identified. Consistent with the view that NPMc ϩ AMLs might derive from a HSC, they show a wide FAB morphologic spectrum and frequent multilineage involvement. A similar HOX signature was previously reported in an uncharacterized subset of AML with normal karyotype. We demonstrate that this is a specific feature of NPMc ϩ AMLs."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Repression of the HSC-associated genes CD34 and CD133/PROM1 is not necessarily in contrast with this view, since a HSC subpopulation negative for both lineage-and HSC-associated markers has been identified."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_6]",
      "span_text": "Consistent with the view that NPMc ϩ AMLs might derive from a HSC, they show a wide FAB morphologic spectrum and frequent multilineage involvement."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_7]",
      "span_text": "Notably, NPMc ϩ AMLs also display induction of the Notch1-ligand JAG1 and repression of CDKN2C/ p18-INK4C, which are associated to expansion of the HSC pool. Repression of the HSC-associated genes CD34 and CD133/PROM1 is not necessarily in contrast with this view, since a HSC subpopulation negative for both lineage-and HSC-associated markers has been identified. Consistent with the view that NPMc ϩ AMLs might derive from a HSC, they show a wide FAB morphologic spectrum and frequent multilineage involvement. A similar HOX signature was previously reported in an uncharacterized subset of AML with normal karyotype."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_8]",
      "span_text": "Acute leukemias carrying MLL rearrangements also display induction of HOX genes, possibly due to direct binding of mixed lineage leukemia (MLL) fusion proteins to HOX promoters. A similar mechanism is not likely for NPMc ϩ AML: NPM is a nuclear chaperone that regulates diverse processes (such as assembly and transport of preribosomal particles, and centrosome duplication ); interacts with tumor suppressors proteins p53, p19, and retinoblastoma pRB; and is crucial for p53 stabilization after stress. Homeobox activation in NPMc ϩ AML might, therefore, reflect the molecular status of the leukemic target cell rather than represent a direct consequence of NPM mutations."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_9]",
      "span_text": "possibly due to direct binding of mixed lineage leukemia (MLL) fusion proteins to HOX promoters."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_10]",
      "span_text": "A similar mechanism is not likely for NPMc ϩ AML: NPM is a nuclear chaperone"
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_11]",
      "span_text": "Acute leukemias carrying MLL rearrangements also display induction of HOX genes, possibly due to direct binding of mixed lineage leukemia (MLL) fusion proteins to HOX promoters. A similar mechanism is not likely for NPMc ϩ AML: NPM is a nuclear chaperone that regulates diverse processes (such as assembly and transport of preribosomal particles, and centrosome duplication ); interacts with tumor suppressors proteins p53, p19, and retinoblastoma pRB; and is crucial for p53 stabilization after stress. Homeobox activation in NPMc ϩ AML might, therefore, reflect the molecular status of the leukemic target cell rather than represent a direct consequence of NPM mutations."
